  "text": "TLS configuration flows through prometheus/prometheus to prometheus-common as follows:\n\n1. **Configuration Definition**: TLS configuration is defined in `config/config.go` (line 33 imports `github.com/prometheus/common/config`). The TLSConfig struct from prometheus-common is embedded within HTTPClientConfig, which is then embedded in:\n   - ScrapeConfig (line 830): `HTTPClientConfig config.HTTPClientConfig` for scrape targets\n   - RemoteWriteConfig (line 1434): `HTTPClientConfig config.HTTPClientConfig` for remote write endpoints\n   - AlertmanagerConfig: `HTTPClientConfig config.HTTPClientConfig` for alertmanager endpoints\n   - TracingConfig (line 1165): Direct `TLSConfig config.TLSConfig` for OTLP tracing\n   - Discovery configs: TLSConfig for service discovery endpoints\n\n2. **Scrape Configuration Flow**:\n   - ScrapeConfig contains HTTPClientConfig with TLSConfig fields (CAFile, CertFile, KeyFile, InsecureSkipVerify, MinVersion, MaxVersion)\n   - scrape/scrape.go line 2260: `newScrapeClient()` receives `config_util.HTTPClientConfig` parameter\n   - Calls `config_util.NewClientFromConfig()` from prometheus-common to create HTTP client with TLS\n\n3. **Remote Write Configuration Flow**:\n   - RemoteWriteConfig contains HTTPClientConfig with TLSConfig\n   - storage/remote/client.go line 184: `NewWriteClient()` receives ClientConfig with HTTPClientConfig\n   - Calls `config_util.NewClientFromConfig()` from prometheus-common to create TLS-enabled HTTP client\n\n4. **Remote Read Configuration Flow**:\n   - storage/remote/client.go line 151: `NewReadClient()` similar to write client\n   - Uses `config_util.NewClientFromConfig()` from prometheus-common\n\n5. **TLS Validation and Application**:\n   - cmd/promtool/main.go line 790: `checkTLSConfig()` validates TLSConfig fields (CertFile/KeyFile pairs)\n   - config/config.go lines 858, 1340, 1473: HTTPClientConfig.Validate() called for RemoteWriteConfig, AlertmanagerConfig, and ScrapeConfig\n   - Actual TLS cert loading and tls.Config creation happens in prometheus-common's NewClientFromConfig function\n\n6. **OTLP Tracing TLS Flow**:\n   - tracing/tracing.go lines 189, 222: Directly calls `config_util.NewTLSConfig()` from prometheus-common\n   - Uses returned tls.Config for gRPC TLS credentials\n\n7. **Service Discovery TLS Flow**:\n   - discovery/triton/triton.go line 154: Calls `config.NewTLSConfig()` for triton discovery\n   - discovery/openstack/openstack.go line 197: Calls `config.NewTLSConfig()` for OpenStack discovery\n   - Returns tls.Config used for HTTP client creation\n\n8. **Alertmanager Configuration Flow**:\n   - notifier/alertmanagerset.go line 51: `newAlertmanagerSet()` calls `config_util.NewClientFromConfig()` for alertmanager endpoints with TLS\n\n**Key Functions from prometheus-common (imported as config_util or config)**:\n- NewClientFromConfig: Creates *http.Client with TLS configured from HTTPClientConfig\n- NewTLSConfig: Creates *tls.Config from TLSConfig struct, handling file loading, version parsing\n- HTTPClientOption: Interface for HTTP client customization\n\nThe TLSConfig struct in prometheus-common contains: CAFile, CertFile, KeyFile, ServerName, InsecureSkipVerify, MinVersion, MaxVersion, and additional fields. These are validated at configuration load time and converted to Go's crypto/tls.Config at client creation time."
}

